  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 15 high, 10 medium, 12 normal. Key bases needing attention include Sibiu (SBZ/LRSB), Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP); plus 14 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Sofia (SOF/LBSF) and M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB). Network hotspots: Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 8 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, cold‑temperature performance penalties and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR) and 9 others.",
